
These issues have the following impacts, which consequently raise risks:


| Issue                                      | Impact                                   | Risk   | Reasoning                                                                           |
| ------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Mode mismatch after reconnect (1/25 cases) | UI and device state inconsistency        | High   | Incorrect mode shown to user, affects trust and correctness of feature              |
| Android mode switch delay (4s vs 2s)       | Performance degradation, slower response | Medium | Functionality works but does not meet timing expectation, affecting user experience |
| iOS battery warning wording                | User confusion                           | Low    | No functional impact, only user experience clarity issue                            |


"Full release" is not recommended due to a core functional inconsistency (UI vs. device state mismatch) that undermines trust and correctness, despite its low frequency.
"No release" is not recommended either as most functionality works correctly and the issues are limited in scope and not fully blocking.

I therefore recommand a "conditional release":
	1.Fix or mitigate the reconnect state mismatch (highest priority).
	2.Investigate the Android performance delay, and adjust it after release if it’s stable.
	3.Improve the iOS battery warning wording in the next release.
